<i>- What? What, I'm fine. I'm fine.</i>

507
00:50:14,644 --> 00:50:16,909
<i>Stop, Mom. Stop.</i>

508
00:50:17,314 --> 00:50:18,839
<i>Oh, look, there's a camera.</i>

509
00:50:19,016 --> 00:50:21,178
<i>- Look, Mom, smile. Smile.</i>
<i>- That's enough.</i>

510
00:50:21,351 --> 00:50:24,378
<i>Hey, Steph, you got a little something</i>
<i>on your face.</i>

511
00:50:24,554 --> 00:50:28,821
<i>- Michael. Turn it off.</i>
<i>- I'm fine. I'm just high.</i>

512
00:50:55,719 --> 00:50:57,483
<i>Are you going to bless the meal?</i>

513
00:51:14,538 --> 00:51:17,337
<i>Michael, turn off the camera.</i>

514
00:52:33,950 --> 00:52:35,543
Okay.

515
00:52:35,785 --> 00:52:37,720
Here's a thousand.

516
00:52:39,256 --> 00:52:40,986
Just like that?

517
00:52:41,158 --> 00:52:44,890
There's another 3 when the deal is done.
That's 5 percent.

518
00:52:48,298 --> 00:52:50,164
Look at you, man.

519
00:52:50,634 --> 00:52:53,001
You ain't from the streets.

520
00:52:55,305 --> 00:52:57,240
What's that mean?

521
00:53:00,644 --> 00:53:03,079
How you know
how to do all this shit?

522
00:53:06,016 --> 00:53:08,485
Might've just got lucky.

523
00:53:09,519 --> 00:53:11,078
So did you, huh?

524
00:53:11,254 --> 00:53:12,847
Word.

525
00:53:14,191 --> 00:53:16,888
So tomorrow at 12.

526
00:53:17,060 --> 00:53:19,825
- Yeah.
- All right, man.

527
00:53:19,996 --> 00:53:23,398
All right. Go to work tonight, buddy.

528
00:53:37,414 --> 00:53:41,579
Michael, can you tell the driver
to take my bags upstairs, please?

529
00:53:44,287 --> 00:53:47,052
Michael, did you hear me?

530
00:53:53,430 --> 00:53:56,264
Smells like smoke in here.

531
00:54:03,807 --> 00:54:07,574
Michael, did you let someone stay here
while we were gone?

532
00:54:07,744 --> 00:54:09,007
No.

533
00:54:09,179 --> 00:54:11,080
He wouldn't do something like that.

534
00:54:11,248 --> 00:54:13,843
What the hell is going on here?

535
00:54:15,885 --> 00:54:20,323
Will someone call Terrence
and ask him if he stayed over?

536
00:54:21,291 --> 00:54:23,089
He wouldn't do that.

537
00:54:23,260 --> 00:54:26,560
Well, if not him, who?

538
00:54:40,510 --> 00:54:42,672
We've been robbed.

539
00:54:43,880 --> 00:54:45,849
Check my jewelry.

540
00:54:47,250 --> 00:54:49,310
It's gone.

541
00:54:49,552 --> 00:54:51,453
All of it.

542
00:54:51,621 --> 00:54:53,522
And your father's ring?

543
00:54:53,690 --> 00:54:55,659
It's gone.

544
00:54:58,695 --> 00:54:59,719
Mom...

545
00:55:00,664 --> 00:55:01,893
...where's your car?

546
00:55:05,468 --> 00:55:06,902
We've been robbed.

547
00:55:07,237 --> 00:55:08,364
What?

548
00:55:18,415 --> 00:55:20,111
Okay.

549
00:56:14,037 --> 00:56:15,130
Hey.

550
00:56:27,450 --> 00:56:29,783
How much to fuck you, right now?

551
00:56:30,420 --> 00:56:31,581
Can't do it, baby.

552
00:56:32,655 --> 00:56:34,146
No?

553
00:56:34,958 --> 00:56:37,325
Come on, everyone's got a price.

554
00:56:37,494 --> 00:56:39,929
My girl's got a price.

555
00:56:40,096 --> 00:56:41,724
I've got a price.

556
00:56:41,898 --> 00:56:43,127
So what's yours?

557
00:56:43,400 --> 00:56:45,631
Two thousand. Cash.

558
00:56:47,704 --> 00:56:51,664
- Done.
- Come on, baby.

559
00:57:15,532 --> 00:57:16,591
Oh, fuck.

560
00:57:20,970 --> 00:57:23,439
Shit. Shit.

561
00:57:27,410 --> 00:57:30,346
- What happened?
- They came home.

562
00:57:30,613 --> 00:57:32,377
- I know.
- Where the fuck were you?

563
00:57:32,549 --> 00:57:35,781
- Where was I? I was setting shit up.
- Too late now, isn't it?

564
00:57:35,952 --> 00:57:37,614
Fuck.

565
00:57:38,021 --> 00:57:39,421
Did you sell the ring?

566
00:57:39,589 --> 00:57:42,684
- What ring?
- Oh, you did. You bastard.

567
00:57:42,859 --> 00:57:44,452
- I didn't sell the ring.
- Liar.

568
00:57:44,627 --> 00:57:47,620
- I don't give a fuck about that ring, okay?
- I did.

569
00:57:47,797 --> 00:57:50,665
Okay, great.
Well, I don't give a fuck about you.

570
00:57:50,834 --> 00:57:52,462
Pull over.

571
00:57:52,869 --> 00:57:54,895
- No, look, I'm sorry--
- Pull over.

572
00:57:55,071 --> 00:57:57,404
All right, look, I'm sorry.
I didn't mean it.

573
00:57:57,574 --> 00:57:59,941
- Fuck you.
- I'm sorry!

574
00:58:00,109 --> 00:58:02,135
Just thank God you weren't pinched.

575
00:58:02,312 --> 00:58:05,339
- They're gonna figure it out, Jonas.
- They probably have.

576
00:58:05,515 --> 00:58:08,246
- Car's gonna be hot in less than an hour.
- Ditch it.

577
00:58:08,418 --> 00:58:11,513
I can't. This is the only thing
I have left in this deal.

578
00:58:13,623 --> 00:58:18,584
I just need to find another one of these
and change the plates. That's it.

579
00:58:18,995 --> 00:58:20,930
Change the plates.

580
00:58:51,961 --> 00:58:53,953
Order me a coffee. I'll be back.

581
00:58:54,130 --> 00:58:56,258
I just need to freshen up a little.

582
00:59:39,976 --> 00:59:41,569
Thanks.

583
01:02:15,364 --> 01:02:19,301
- Hi. Could I get one to see <i>The Kid?</i>
- Hi. Sure. Nine dollars.

584
01:04:27,530 --> 01:04:28,554
It's an old print.

585
01:04:30,833 --> 01:04:33,234
They break sometimes.

586
01:04:33,402 --> 01:04:34,961
Yeah.

587
01:04:38,241 --> 01:04:39,766
<i>Excuse me. Miss.</i>

588
01:04:40,209 --> 01:04:42,940
You don't look like
a big Charlie Chaplin fan.

589
01:04:43,112 --> 01:04:44,136
A fan?

590
01:04:44,313 --> 01:04:46,282
That's a pretty old film.

591
01:04:46,716 --> 01:04:48,241
Yeah.

592
01:04:48,417 --> 01:04:50,477
I didn't think it would be that sad.

593
01:04:50,953 --> 01:04:52,615
Do I know you from somewhere?

594
01:04:53,689 --> 01:04:56,488
- I don't think so.
- I'm Michael.

595
01:04:58,294 --> 01:04:59,922
Kelly.

596
01:05:00,630 --> 01:05:02,394
Hi, Kelly.

597
01:05:04,033 --> 01:05:05,763
Do you drink coffee, Kelly?

598
01:05:05,935 --> 01:05:07,164
Yeah.

599
01:05:07,336 --> 01:05:09,771
- But I think I should go.
- Please?

600
01:05:10,339 --> 01:05:11,967
- Oh, I gotta go--
- Come on.

601
01:05:12,141 --> 01:05:14,110
I'll tell you how the film ends.

602
01:05:18,948 --> 01:05:20,007
Okay.

603
01:05:20,182 --> 01:05:21,673
Okay?

604
01:05:23,052 --> 01:05:24,543
Come on.

605
01:05:26,856 --> 01:05:29,121
This is really great, you know?

606
01:05:29,392 --> 01:05:30,826
What?

607
01:05:30,993 --> 01:05:33,087
A beautiful girl went to see
a Charlie Chaplin movie.

608
01:05:33,930 --> 01:05:35,762
What's so great about that?

609
01:05:35,932 --> 01:05:38,265
Girls like you get into bars
without waiting.

610
01:05:38,434 --> 01:05:42,701
They don't go to old black and white
movies on the big screen by themselves.

611
01:05:42,872 --> 01:05:44,170
You don't know me.

612
01:05:44,807 --> 01:05:46,503
Oh, yeah?

613
01:05:46,776 --> 01:05:48,176
So who are you?

614
01:05:50,780 --> 01:05:52,544
I'm nobody.

615
01:05:53,883 --> 01:05:54,942
I should go.

616
01:05:55,117 --> 01:05:58,610
I'm sorry. I didn't mean
to make you feel uncomfortable.

617
01:05:59,255 --> 01:06:01,554
At least let me walk you home. It's late.

618
01:06:01,724 --> 01:06:03,522
I'm fine.

619
01:06:03,893 --> 01:06:06,158
Well, will you let me give you a ride?

620
01:06:06,429 --> 01:06:08,854
- Is this yours?
- Yeah.

621
01:06:09,031 --> 01:06:11,432
It drives better than it looks.

622
01:06:28,851 --> 01:06:31,252
I got a surprise for you.

623
01:06:36,826 --> 01:06:38,886
It's beautiful, isn't it?

624
01:06:39,428 --> 01:06:40,919
Yeah.

625
01:06:41,263 --> 01:06:42,629
I love it up here.

626
01:06:42,798 --> 01:06:44,926
I used to come here a lot.

627
01:06:46,102 --> 01:06:48,071
Why not anymore?

628
01:06:49,872 --> 01:06:51,932
Part of another life.

629
01:07:03,219 --> 01:07:07,156
- Sorry, I didn't mean to bring up anything.
- It's okay.

630
01:07:07,323 --> 01:07:09,155
It's over now.

631
01:07:12,962 --> 01:07:15,727
Do you have a girlfriend?

632
01:07:16,332 --> 01:07:17,823
No.

633
01:07:19,402 --> 01:07:22,270
I did. We broke up about a year ago.

634
01:07:24,040 --> 01:07:25,565
Why?

635
01:07:28,044 --> 01:07:30,912
She just couldn't handle it.

636
01:07:32,815 --> 01:07:33,908
Handle what?

637
01:07:34,950 --> 01:07:36,885
I had a sister...

638
01:07:37,219 --> 01:07:40,246
...but she died about three years ago.

639
01:07:40,890 --> 01:07:42,222
I'm sorry.

640
01:07:42,391 --> 01:07:44,292
It's okay.

641
01:07:44,593 --> 01:07:46,619
She got into drugs.

642
01:07:48,731 --> 01:07:50,131
Lot of people do.

643
01:07:50,299 --> 01:07:51,733
Yeah.

644
01:07:52,902 --> 01:07:58,671
It's crazy. If you would've met Steph,
you'd never think that she'd...

645
01:07:58,841 --> 01:08:00,742
It just happens.

646
01:08:00,910 --> 01:08:05,814
Sometimes you don't know what's gonna
hook you until you try it, then it's too late.

647
01:08:08,784 --> 01:08:10,844
Yeah, I guess.

648
01:08:46,155 --> 01:08:47,817
Oh, shit.

649
01:08:47,990 --> 01:08:49,720
Wake up. Wake up. Shit.

650
01:08:50,059 --> 01:08:51,960
Shit, shit, shit.

651
01:08:52,128 --> 01:08:53,926
Sorry.

652
01:08:54,396 --> 01:08:56,365
I'm so late. Shit.

653
01:08:56,532 --> 01:08:57,830
Come on.

654
01:09:13,883 --> 01:09:15,943
I'm so late. I'm sorry.

655
01:09:16,552 --> 01:09:20,250
I have to meet my dad all the way
downtown. Are you hungry?

656
01:09:20,422 --> 01:09:22,482
You can help yourself to the fridge...

657
01:09:22,658 --> 01:09:24,854
...or take a shower, anything, okay?

658
01:09:25,027 --> 01:09:27,019
- I won't be gone very long.
- Thanks.

659
01:09:35,671 --> 01:09:40,200
- Okay. I gotta go. You good?
- Yeah.

660
01:09:40,376 --> 01:09:42,368
- You sure?
- Yeah.

661
01:09:42,845 --> 01:09:44,336
Okay.

662
01:09:45,781 --> 01:09:47,841
Will you have dinner with me tonight?

663
01:09:49,118 --> 01:09:50,848
- Sure.
- Yeah?

664
01:09:51,153 --> 01:09:52,746
Okay. Okay.

665
01:09:54,356 --> 01:09:56,222
Okay. Bye.

666
01:10:32,895 --> 01:10:34,659
<i>Thank you.</i>

667
01:10:38,901 --> 01:10:40,199
That's it.

668
01:10:40,369 --> 01:10:42,600
That's Wong's factory.

669
01:10:42,771 --> 01:10:44,501
The Chinese order is confirmed.

670
01:10:44,673 --> 01:10:45,834
That's great.

671
01:10:46,375 --> 01:10:48,139
I just wish we didn't have...

672
01:10:48,310 --> 01:10:51,678
...to come all the way back home
to get that done, but...

673
01:10:52,348 --> 01:10:53,976
Is there any news on the house?

674
01:10:54,149 --> 01:10:58,644
Yeah. Yeah.
They said that it was not uncommon.

675
01:10:58,821 --> 01:11:00,915
You know, things are bad...

676
01:11:01,090 --> 01:11:04,288
...and these things happen.
Terrence got a good look at them.

677
01:11:04,593 --> 01:11:06,494
- Wait, what?
- Yeah.

678
01:11:06,662 --> 01:11:10,121
He spoke to them. Said they were
a very nice looking young couple.

679
01:11:10,299 --> 01:11:13,064
They called themselves
Adam and Sarah, your cousins.

680
01:11:13,235 --> 01:11:15,500
- They did their homework.
- You're kidding?

681
01:11:15,671 --> 01:11:18,607
And he, the kid,
knew what he was doing.

682
01:11:18,774 --> 01:11:22,870
He got my passwords,
he got into my files, he got my gun.

683
01:11:23,045 --> 01:11:24,570
- The old six-shooter.
- Yeah.

684
01:11:24,747 --> 01:11:26,875
Surprised he didn't blow his hand off.

685
01:11:27,383 --> 01:11:30,649
It's all right. Everything's insured.

686
01:11:30,819 --> 01:11:33,812
Except for my father's ring.

687
01:11:35,291 --> 01:11:37,658
Shit. Sorry, Dad.

688
01:11:42,631 --> 01:11:44,327
Wait a minute.

689
01:11:44,500 --> 01:11:48,961
She came into the theater
and sat down right next to you?

690
01:11:49,605 --> 01:11:53,235
Didn't sit down right next to me.
She was the only person in there.

691
01:11:53,642 --> 01:11:55,201
- To see <i>The Kid?</i>
- Yeah.

692
01:11:55,377 --> 01:11:57,812
- Unbelievable.
- I know, right?

693
01:11:57,980 --> 01:12:01,348
Well, she sounds pretty interesting.

694
01:12:01,517 --> 01:12:03,213
Yeah, she's...

695
01:12:03,385 --> 01:12:05,445
She's interesting.

696
01:12:07,723 --> 01:12:08,782
And?

697
01:12:08,957 --> 01:12:10,516
And...

698
01:12:10,693 --> 01:12:13,720
- ...we're having dinner tonight.
- Yeah.

699
01:12:13,896 --> 01:12:16,161
That's the way it starts.

700
01:12:17,166 --> 01:12:19,101
- What's that?
- Love.

701
01:12:19,268 --> 01:12:21,737
- Dad. Come on.
- No, that's the way love starts.

702
01:12:22,438 --> 01:12:24,737
How do you know it's love, though?

703
01:12:25,207 --> 01:12:26,766
Well...

704
01:12:27,376 --> 01:12:31,507
...for someone to find true love
in their twenties, that's rare.

705
01:12:31,780 --> 01:12:35,774
So if it's not true love,
at least it's great practice.

706
01:12:35,951 --> 01:12:38,216
And if it is true love...

707
01:12:38,520 --> 01:12:40,489
...then it's a blessing.

708
01:12:40,823 --> 01:12:43,054
And you can't ignore that.

709
01:13:57,866 --> 01:14:02,065
- Hi. Can I get a one way to Barstow?
- Fifty-five.

710
01:14:54,957 --> 01:14:56,619
I'm sorry.

711
01:14:56,792 --> 01:14:58,488
I tried.

712
01:15:57,686 --> 01:15:59,211
Hey.

713
01:15:59,821 --> 01:16:00,914
You okay?

714
01:16:01,857 --> 01:16:03,086
Yeah.

715
01:16:03,258 --> 01:16:04,783
I'm good.

716
01:16:07,029 --> 01:16:09,225
What are your plans today?

717
01:16:09,598 --> 01:16:11,226
I don't know.

718
01:16:14,536 --> 01:16:16,596
Will you spend the day with me?

719
01:17:41,189 --> 01:17:43,090
This is nice.

720
01:17:49,765 --> 01:17:51,233
What?

721
01:17:56,338 --> 01:17:58,898
I love spending time with you.

722
01:18:12,087 --> 01:18:14,352
Will you go to dinner with me tonight?

723
01:18:14,756 --> 01:18:16,452
Okay.

724
01:18:16,992 --> 01:18:18,688
At my parents' house?

725
01:18:19,227 --> 01:18:20,820
Yeah, I know it sounds weird.

726
01:18:20,996 --> 01:18:23,795
It's a Passover dinner.
It's a religious thing...

727
01:18:23,965 --> 01:18:25,866
...but it'll be fun.

728
01:18:26,735 --> 01:18:28,397
I don't know.

729
01:18:29,171 --> 01:18:30,969
I don't think that's a good idea.

730
01:18:31,139 --> 01:18:32,767
Why not?

731
01:18:33,341 --> 01:18:34,741
I don't know. I--

732
01:18:34,910 --> 01:18:38,642
Listen. You have nothing
to worry about. They're really nice.

733
01:18:38,814 --> 01:18:42,046
And I just-- I'd like you to meet them.

734
01:18:42,451 --> 01:18:43,475
Please?

735
01:18:46,254 --> 01:18:48,120
Let me think about it, okay?

736
01:18:48,290 --> 01:18:50,088
Okay.

737
01:19:09,177 --> 01:19:10,270
Ronald, what's up?

738
01:19:10,445 --> 01:19:13,210
Where the bloody hell
is my Porsche Carrera?

739
01:19:13,381 --> 01:19:15,543
Look, there was a bit of a problem.

740
01:19:15,717 --> 01:19:17,583
But here's what I'm gonna do, okay?

741
01:19:17,753 --> 01:19:22,657
I'm gonna sell you the Cayenne for half
and then we'll just call it even. Cool?

742
01:19:25,026 --> 01:19:27,154
Are you fucking kidding me?

743
01:19:27,329 --> 01:19:29,161
No, it's a good car.

744
01:19:29,331 --> 01:19:32,665
I wouldn't give that car to my mother.

745
01:19:32,834 --> 01:19:34,496
Do I look like a soccer mommy?

746
01:19:34,669 --> 01:19:37,867
- "Get in the back of the car, kids."
- No.

747
01:19:38,940 --> 01:19:40,306
- We made a deal...
- I know.

748
01:19:40,475 --> 01:19:42,000
...for the Porsche Carrera.

749
01:19:42,177 --> 01:19:44,646
There was a problem, all right, man?
I'm sorry.

750
01:19:44,813 --> 01:19:46,975
I can sell you this for half.

751
01:19:47,816 --> 01:19:50,684
- You believe this guy, Sammy?
- Well, it's a good car.

752
01:19:50,852 --> 01:19:51,979
Go on, sunshine.

753
01:19:52,154 --> 01:19:53,383
Oh, whoa, hey, hey.

754
01:19:53,555 --> 01:19:55,319
No, no, no, please don't.

755
01:19:55,490 --> 01:19:56,981
I can get it.

756
01:19:57,159 --> 01:19:59,355
I can get you the car. I'll get it.

757
01:19:59,528 --> 01:20:01,224
- I will take a finger...
- No.

758
01:20:01,396 --> 01:20:05,891
...for every day that you do not bring me
my Porsche Carrera.

759
01:20:06,067 --> 01:20:09,196
No, please, I'll get it.
I'll get the Carrera, I'll get it.

760
01:20:09,371 --> 01:20:10,464
I'll get it.

761
01:20:10,639 --> 01:20:13,575
- Told you not to fuck with me, right?
- Yes, and I won't.

762
01:20:13,742 --> 01:20:17,304
- Yeah? Did I not?
- I'll get it, I'll get it.

763
01:20:17,479 --> 01:20:20,540
Not so fucking shiny and smooth now,
are you, motherfucker?

764
01:20:20,715 --> 01:20:21,978
Okay.

765
01:20:22,150 --> 01:20:23,174
Okay, I'll get it.

